<subSubSection id="C30A6528FFB0FF82C5931FBBFC98FA26" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAF36A3FFB0FF82C5931FBBFC3FFB7E" blockId="18.[136,1089,980,1443]" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">
Taxonomic notes. Numerous subspecies of this externally strikingly variable species are described. The nominotypical subspecies is restricted to the eastern periphery of the Austrian Alps. Further subspecies occur in the Central and western Alps, and Alsace (
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB0FF82C7151855FF41FBF0" authority="Schawerda, 1925" authorityName="Schawerda" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="helvetica">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB0FF82C7151855FC2BFBD6" box="[579,937,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Mamestra serratilinea helvetica</emphasis>
Schawerda, 1925
</taxonomicName>
), Balkan peninsula (
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB0FF82C4951835FC72FBF1" authority="Drenovsky, 1931" authorityName="Drenovsky" authorityYear="1931" box="[451,1008,1114,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="kowatschevi">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB0FF82C4951835FC96FBF1" box="[451,788,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea kowatschevi</emphasis>
Drenovsky, 1931
</taxonomicName>
), Central 
<collectingCountry id="F3077633FFB0FF82C5E11813FEA0FB13" box="[183,290,1148,1174]" name="Turkey" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB0FF82C4671813FD5FFB13" authority="Varga, 1974" authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="1974" box="[305,733,1148,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="pinkeri">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB0FF82C4671813FDC7FB13" box="[305,581,1148,1174]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea pinkeri</emphasis>
Varga, 1974
</taxonomicName>
), and more clearly differenti- ated in Central Asia (
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB0FF82C4C718F2FC08FB3D" authority="(Alpheraky, 1887)" baseAuthorityName="Alpheraky" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[401,906,1181,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="spalax">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB0FF82C4C718F2FD20FB32" box="[401,674,1181,1207]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea spalax</emphasis>
(Alphéraky, 1887)
</taxonomicName>
, in the Hindukush-Himalaya area (
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB0FF82C4C418D0FB86FB5C" authority="Hacker et Weigert, 1990" authorityName="Hacker et Weigert" authorityYear="1990" box="[402,1028,1215,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="tenebricosa">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB0FF82C4C418D0FD57FB5C" box="[402,725,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea tenebricosa</emphasis>
Hacker et Weigert, 1990
</taxonomicName>
), but also in western 
<collectingCountry id="F3077633FFB0FF82C41F188EFE42FB7E" box="[329,448,1249,1275]" name="Mongolia" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB0FF82C486188EFC33FB7E" authority="Varga, 1974" authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="1974" box="[464,945,1249,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="serratilinea" subSpecies="eremorealis">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB0FF82C486188EFC9AFB7E" box="[464,792,1249,1275]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">Polia serratilinea eremorealis</emphasis>
Varga, 1974
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36A3FFB0FF82C593196DFC98FA26" blockId="18.[136,1089,980,1443]" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">
This species shows some convergence to 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB0FF82C7E9196CFCC1FA99" authorityName="McCabe" authorityYear="1980" box="[703,835,1282,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="53" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="propodea">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB0FF82C7E9196CFCC1FA99" box="[703,835,1282,1308]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="53">P. propodea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the bifid terminal part of the right saccular process.The two lineages are, however, rather distant by their CO1 sequences. The asymmetrisation of the clavus and saccular processes show an evident geographical variation; its analysis and taxonomic interpretation will be treated in a further publication.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
